userStories.notes:
Files:
- plugins/amplitude/src/amplitude-api.ts (add guard before line 106 return)

Context:
gql() at line 74 makes a fetchFromPage call and parses JSON. The guard at line 97 is:
  if (json.errors?.length && !json.data) { throw ... }
  return json.data as T;

When the Amplitude API returns {} (no data, no errors), json.errors is undefined and json.data is undefined. The guard on line 97 is NOT triggered (json.errors is falsy), so json.data (undefined) is returned as T. Any tool handler that does const { foo } = await gql(...) crashes with TypeError: Cannot destructure property 'foo' of undefined.

Changes:
After the existing errors guard at line 97, add a check:
  if (json.data === undefined) {
    throw ToolError.internal('GraphQL response contained neither data nor errors');
  }
  return json.data as T;

Constraints:
- Do NOT change the error handling for the existing errors-only case (line 97-104)
- Do NOT change the auth error detection logic
- The function signature and callers must not change
